{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Recognise garlic and onion allergies within UK food allergen regulations",
        "additional_details": "Garlic and onion allergies are common, yet they're not legally recognised. These ingredients are often invisible in meals, so people can\u2019t detect them when food is served. Restaurants rely on allergen lists that don\u2019t include them, leading to mistakes and illness. Recognition would improve labelling, training and safety.",
        "background": "Garlic and onion allergies can cause severe reactions, but they aren\u2019t recognised in current allergen rules. This means restaurants and food labels often don\u2019t list them, putting people at risk. Recognition would improve safety, awareness and consistency.",
